tg-ws-proxy-pc
==============

A desktop (Windows / Linux / macOS) edition of the tg-ws-proxy MTProto proxy
for Telegram. Distributed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 — see
LICENSE.

Lineage
-------

  Flowseal/tg-ws-proxy            original project, MIT License
    └─ amurcanov/tg-ws-proxy-android   Android port + Rust engine, GPL-3.0
         └─ North-web-dev/tg-ws-proxy-pc   this repository — desktop CLI + GUI

This repository is a fork of amurcanov/tg-ws-proxy-android and inherits its
GPL-3.0 license. The Rust proxy engine (src/proxy.rs, ws.rs, cfproxy.rs,
crypto.rs, balancer.rs, config.rs) originates upstream and is reused unchanged.

Changes made in this fork
-------------------------

  * Added a native Rust API (src/runner.rs) around the engine so desktop
    front-ends drive it directly instead of through the Android JNI C ABI.
  * Added a headless CLI front-end (src/bin/cli.rs).
  * Added a GUI front-end using egui/eframe (src/bin/gui.rs).
  * Reworked the crate as a library + two binaries; kept the `cdylib` target
    so the original Android/JNI build path still links.
  * Removed Android-only build tooling (Gradle project, JNI shims, legacy Go).

